    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Egan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan is instructed to report to the Department the names of the refugees
                        in his legation and the offices they have filled, the crimes they are
                        accused of, and whether process from any regular tribunal has issued against
                        them. He is also directed to report the conduct of the ministers of other
                        countries, whether persons have taken refuge in their legations, and, if so,
                        the action of the Chilean Government respecting them; and to promptly and
                        fully inform the Department of all facts.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
